            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001273_0001" n="0001"/><!-- Change both @facs and @n -->
	<!-- Start each page with a <pb> formatted as above -->

<!-- If this is a letter or similar with an opener (with content such as dateline and/or salute) add it. For example: -->

<lb/><opener><dateline rend="right"><placeName><settlement type="town">Birkenhead</settlement></placeName> <add place="above" hand="#U">7</add>
<lb/><seg rend="left diagonal"><add hand="#U"><hi rend="underline">3</hi></add></seg> <date when="1858-03-06">6<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> March 
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/> 1858</date></dateline>
<lb/>   
<lb/><salute>My Dear <persName>Agnes</persName></salute></opener><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->

<lb/><p>The Pearl went 
<lb/>out of dock
<lb/>today <!--Uses a plus size in the letter, should this be denoted with a "&amp;" JZ?--><!-- Yes. AW --> &amp; sails 
<lb/>on <choice><sic>monday</sic><corr>Monday</corr></choice>
<lb/>forenoon, We
<lb/>go on <unclear cert="high">board</unclear>
<lb/>at 8 in the morning 

	<pb facs="liv_001273_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/><persName>Mama</persName><!-- gray area --> has been
<lb/>putting all the
<lb/>things in the
<lb/>cabin in order
<lb/>and sends her
<lb/>love</p>        	
<lb/><p>Now you
<lb/>are commmitted
<lb/>to the care of
<lb/>God Almighty
<lb/>May he give

	<pb facs="liv_001273_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>you much
<lb/>grace and 
<lb/>be merciful
<lb/>to you - <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>Write
<lb/>to <persName>Robert</persName>
<lb/>Never do 
<lb/>anything you
<lb/>would be
<lb/>ashamed to
<lb/><gap extent="2" unit="lines" agent="hole"/>

	<pb facs="liv_001273_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>and may the
<lb/>Lord be very 
<lb/>gracious to you
<lb/><!--Unsure if this is a paragraph break. JZ--><!--I don't believe so, usually a bit more space if it's a paragraph break, I've seen. BL-->Kind <unclear cert="high">regards</unclear>
<lb/>to your <term type="occupation">teacher</term>
<lb/><!--Uses a plus size in the letter, should this be denoted with a "&amp;"?-->&amp; <unclear cert="high">friends</unclear> also
<lb/>to <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">rs</hi> Buchanan</persName> 
<lb/>when you see
<lb/>her</p><closer><salute>I am</salute> &amp;
<lb/><gap extent="2" unit="lines" agent="hole"/><supplied cert="high"><persName>David Livingstone</persName></supplied></closer>

        	</div>
